# Portal MCP Server Configurations
# Copy these values into Open WebUI Admin Panel > Settings > Tools > Add Tool Server
# (Automated setup via openwebui-init handles this on first launch — this file is
#  for reference and manual fallback only.)

# === Image Generation (ComfyUI) ===
# Name: Portal ComfyUI
# URL: http://host.docker.internal:8910/mcp
# API Key: (leave empty)

# === Video Generation (Wan2.2 via ComfyUI) ===
# Name: Portal Video
# URL: http://host.docker.internal:8911/mcp
# API Key: (leave empty)

# === Music Generation (AudioCraft) ===
# Name: Portal Music
# URL: http://host.docker.internal:8912/mcp
# API Key: (leave empty)

# === Document Creation (Word/Excel/PowerPoint) ===
# Name: Portal Documents
# URL: http://host.docker.internal:8913/mcp
# API Key: (leave empty)

# === Code Sandbox (isolated DinD execution) ===
# Name: Portal Code
# URL: http://host.docker.internal:8914/mcp
# API Key: (leave empty)

# === Speech-to-Text (faster-whisper) ===
# Name: Portal Whisper
# URL: http://host.docker.internal:8915/mcp
# API Key: (leave empty)

# === Text-to-Speech (kokoro-onnx / fish-speech) ===
# Name: Portal TTS
# URL: http://host.docker.internal:8916/mcp
# API Key: (leave empty)

# ── Linux users ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Replace host.docker.internal with your host IP:
#   $(ip route | awk '/default/{print $3}')
